Key Match Events: Grant McCray hit a 3-run homer off Dylan Cease in the 2nd inning and a 2-run blast off Yuki Matsui in the 9th inning for the first multi-homer game of his big league career.
Post-Match Reflections: The Mets have won nine straight games to knock the Braves out of the final spot. New York owns the season tiebreaker against the Friars so if they end up with the same record it would be the Mets who get the higher seed.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Padres are in a stretch where they'll play the Giants six times in eight games and not have to face former Friar Blake Snell one time.
San Diego owns the 4th seed and has a 2.0 game lead on the Diamondbacks.
